-- Rain Stops Play in French Open Final for Second Time
-- B y   D a n i e l l e   R o s s i n g h
-- 2012-06-10T16:55:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-10/rain-stops-play-in-french-open-final-for-second-time.html
Rain has halted play in the men’s
French Open finals at  Roland Garros  for the second time.  Defending men’s champion Rafael Nadal of Spain is leading
top-ranked Novak Djokovic of Serbia by two sets to love, and 2-1
down in the fourth set.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Danielle Rossingh at 
 drossingh@bloomberg.net  